 frontend
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

ML:
- Rewrite inference.py to use CropDiseaseFusionModel (EfficientNet-B4 + mBERT)
  instead of the stale ResNet50+LoRA path — aligns with train.py/finetune.py
- Add per-district LoRA adapter injection in InferenceEngine.load_model()
- inference.py now correctly uses all 3 modalities: image, symptom_text, context

Models:
- Fix adapter_config.json: base_model_name_or_path was null → 'models/base/best_model.pth'
- Fix adapter_config.json: task_type was null → 'FEATURE_EXTRACTION'
- Update target_modules from stale ResNet50 conv layers to fusion model linear layers
- Update auto_mapping to CropDiseaseFusionModel

Tests:
- Update test_inference.py: consistent with new InferenceEngine API, adds Hindi
  symptom text example and proper multi-modal test call

Frontend:
- Fix package.json: Next.js 16.2.9 (non-existent) → 15.2.4 (latest stable)
- Fix eslint-config-next to match Next.js version

Infrastructure:
- Rewrite docker-compose.yml: add backend + frontend service definitions
- Move all credentials from hardcoded values to ${ENV_VAR} references
- Add healthcheck for backend service

New files:
- .env.example: template for all required environment variables
- .gitignore: covers Python, Node, model weights, .env, uploads, DB files
- README.md: full project overview, architecture, quickstart, API reference
- ml/requirements.txt: all ML dependencies (torch, transformers, peft, etc.)

Updated:
- backend/requirements.txt: add asyncpg for production PostgreSQL
